sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist<br/>Browser
    participant Gateway as Gateway<br/>data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>OAuth2/OIDC
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>kube-rbac-proxy
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant NotebookCtrl as Notebook Controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Notebook as JupyterLab Pod<br/>8888/TCP HTTP<br/>mTLS optional
    participant TrainingOp as Training Operator<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant TrainingJob as PyTorchJob Pods<br/>Distributed Training
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>AWS IAM Auth
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>REST + gRPC
    participant KServe as KServe Controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant ModelCtrl as ODH Model Controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Predictor as Predictor Pod<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>mTLS optional
    participant Client as External Client<br/>Inference API

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over User,Dashboard: Workflow 1: User Authentication (RHOAI 3.x)
        User->>Gateway: 1. GET /dashboard<br/>No session cookie
        Gateway->>AuthProxy: 2. EnvoyFilter ext_authz check<br/>HTTPS request
        AuthProxy-->>Gateway: 3. Unauthorized (no cookie)
        Gateway-->>User: 4. Redirect to OIDC Provider<br/>Login page
        User->>AuthProxy: 5. OAuth callback with code<br/>POST /oauth/callback
        AuthProxy->>K8sAPI: 6. Validate user permissions<br/>SubjectAccessReview
        K8sAPI-->>AuthProxy: 7. User authorized
        AuthProxy-->>User: 8. Set session cookie<br/>Redirect to /dashboard
        User->>Gateway: 9. GET /dashboard (with cookie)
        Gateway->>AuthProxy: 10. EnvoyFilter ext_authz check
        AuthProxy-->>Gateway: 11. Authorized
        Gateway->>Dashboard: 12. Forward request<br/>kube-rbac-proxy validates
        Dashboard-->>User: 13. Dashboard UI (React SPA)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 250, 240)
        Note over User,Notebook: Workflow 2: Launch Jupyter Workbench
        User->>Dashboard: 14. POST /api/notebooks<br/>Create workbench
        Dashboard->>K8sAPI: 15. Create Notebook CR<br/>Bearer token auth
        K8sAPI->>NotebookCtrl: 16. Watch event: Notebook created
        NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: 17. Create StatefulSet + Service<br/>+ HTTPRoute
        K8sAPI->>Notebook: 18. Pod scheduled and started
        Notebook->>K8sAPI: 19. Readiness probe success
        User->>Gateway: 20. GET /notebook-name/lab<br/>Via HTTPRoute
        Gateway->>Notebook: 21. Forward to JupyterLab<br/>kube-rbac-proxy auth
        Notebook-->>User: 22. JupyterLab interface
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Notebook,S3: Workflow 3: Distributed Model Training
        Notebook->>K8sAPI: 23. Submit PyTorchJob CR<br/>kubectl apply
        K8sAPI->>TrainingOp: 24. Watch event: PyTorchJob created
        TrainingOp->>K8sAPI: 25. Create master + worker pods
        K8sAPI->>TrainingJob: 26. Pods start (gang scheduling)
        TrainingJob->>S3: 27. Download training dataset<br/>HTTPS (AWS SigV4)
        S3-->>TrainingJob: 28. Dataset artifacts
        TrainingJob->>TrainingJob: 29. Distributed training<br/>PyTorch DDP
        TrainingJob->>S3: 30. Upload model checkpoints<br/>HTTPS
        TrainingJob->>ModelReg: 31. POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/registered_models<br/>Register trained model
        ModelReg-->>TrainingJob: 32. Model metadata stored
        TrainingJob-->>K8sAPI: 33. PyTorchJob status: Succeeded
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 240)
        Note over User,Client: Workflow 4: Model Deployment and Inference
        User->>Dashboard: 34. POST /api/serving<br/>Deploy InferenceService
        Dashboard->>K8sAPI: 35. Create InferenceService CR
        K8sAPI->>KServe: 36. Watch: InferenceService created
        KServe->>K8sAPI: 37. Create Deployment + Service<br/>(raw mode default)
        KServe->>S3: 38. Storage Initializer downloads model<br/>HTTPS
        S3-->>KServe: 39. Model artifacts
        K8sAPI->>ModelCtrl: 40. Watch: InferenceService created
        ModelCtrl->>K8sAPI: 41. Create Route + ServiceMonitor<br/>+ NetworkPolicy
        K8sAPI->>Predictor: 42. Predictor pod started<br/>Model loaded
        Predictor-->>K8sAPI: 43. Readiness probe: /v1/models/ready
        Client->>Gateway: 44. POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>HTTPS (Bearer token optional)
        Gateway->>Predictor: 45. Forward to predictor<br/>Via HTTPRoute
        Predictor->>Predictor: 46. Model inference
        Predictor-->>Client: 47. JSON prediction response
    end

    rect rgb(250, 240, 255)
        Note over Client,ModelReg: Workflow 5: ML Pipeline Orchestration (via DSP)
        Note right of User: Pipeline submitted via Dashboard<br/>creates Argo Workflow which:<br/>1) Trains model (TrainingJob)<br/>2) Registers in Model Registry<br/>3) Deploys to KServe<br/>4) Runs validation tests<br/>See DSP component for details
    end
